ynamic and important wine producer was obliterated, tearing apart the local economy and changing a way of life that had lasted for nearly a century.Drawing on archival research as well as interviews with many of the principal players, Thomas Pellechia skillfully traces the economic dynamism of the Finger Lakes wine region, the passion and ingenuity of the Taylor family, and the shortsighted corporate takeover scenario that took down a once-proud American family company. In addition to providing important lessons for business innovators, Over a Barrel is a cautionary tale for a wine region that is repeating its formative history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aWine industryxHistoryxNew York (State)xNew York (State). 0aWine industryzNew York (State)xHistory. 4aAmerican Studies : American Studies. 4aBusiness and Economics : Business History. 4aCultural Studies : Food. 4aHistory : American History. 4aNew York/Regional : New York/Regional. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2015z978311149061840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845551840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438455518423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438455518/original  a978-3-11-149061-8  SUNY Press eBook Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles